  {
    "index": 3,
    "hash": "eCdfpEctHIfWu+kyzlw/osTlcnY=",
    "timestampUtcMs": "2026-05-13T13:00:29.000Z",
    "action": {
      "type": "SET_CONTENT",
      "input": {
        "content": "Chat separates live transport from durable history:\n\n- **Live 1-to-1 messaging** uses PSS (Postal Service over Swarm) on topic `ph:v2:chat:<sorted(A,B)>`. Mined Trojan chunks carry the live stream with 2\u201310s latency.\n- **Chat history** persists on `ph:v2:chatlog:<sorted(A,B)>[:chapter]` as an ACT-protected feed. Each feed update points to a small wrapper chunk containing `actRef || actHistoryAddress` \u2014 self-contained so both parties can decode without side-channel state.\n- **Chapter rotation** on Clear-All-Chats: the chapter value (a `Date.now()` millisecond, stored in localStorage but reconstructable from its strictly increasing property) is appended to the feed topic. Clearing bumps the chapter, making the new feed a genuinely new namespace. Peers learn the new chapter from the first PSS message after clear.\n- **Session recovery** reads `chatPeers[]` from the user manifest, so a fresh browser rehydrates all known conversations from wallet + Bee alone.\n- **Attachments**: raw files via ACT-protected `/bzz` (grantees = recipient's Bee pubkey); document shares reuse the sharing flow.\n- **GSOC notifications** (typing, presence, delivery, doc-updated) exist on the adapter and are the transport for upcoming live-collab work.",
        "updatedAt": "2026-05-13T13:00:29.000Z"
      },
      "timestampUtcMs": "2026-05-13T13:00:29.000Z"
    }
  },
